&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Hello blink-dev!
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This very simple feature adds display-p3-linear as a CSS color space.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This has been added to the CSS specification and has a bazillion WPT 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; tests
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; from:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12596"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12596&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; It has been requested as a candidate for interop 2026:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/web-platform-tests/interop/issues/1167"&gt;https://github.com/web-platform-tests/interop/issues/1167&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; More relevant to the topics close to my heart are the fact that this
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; is a very good space for physically based rendering and high dynamic 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; range.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Adding this space to the list of canvas spaces is a separate feature over
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; at:
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://chromestatus.com/feature/5122501071994880"&gt;https://chromestatus.com/feature/5122501071994880&lt;/a&gt;
